label: Book of hours (Dutch), LTK 299

metadata.label: Author/creator
value: Scribe of Leiden, UB : ms. Ltk 299.

metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Book of hours in the Dutch translation/adaptation by Geert Grote. Without calendar. Contains: (ff. 1r-40r) Hours of the Virgin. - (ff. 41r-65v) Hours of the Cross. - (ff. 66r-92r) Hours of the Holy Gost. - (ff. 93r-115r) Hours of the Eternal Wisdom. - (116r-135v) Penitential Psalms and Litany of the Saints. Incomplete (without beginning). - (ff. 136r-172v) Office of the Dead. Incomplete. - (ff. 172v-176r) Communion prayers. - Also contains some short prayers added by another hand on ff. 40r-v, 65v, 92v, 115v, 135v. - Empty: f. 176v.

metadata.label: Note
value: Origin: Based on the style of the decoration, possibly produced by the Domus Parva in Zwolle. See Wierda 1995.

Script: The scribe of LTK 2199 als wrote: Assen, Drents Archief, Oldenhuis Gratama 929; Berlijn, SBB, Germ. Oct. 7; Leeuwarden, Tresoar, 689 Hs; Londen, VAM, 600-1889; St. Petersburg, BAN, O 254; Utrecht, MCC, ABM 72 (cf. BNM database).

Textual: (f. 1r) "Hier beghint onser vrouwen getide". - (f. 41r) "Hier beghint die cruus ghetijde". - (f. 66r) "Hier begint hilige gheestes tijde". - (f. 93r) "Hier begint die wijsheit getijde". - (f. 136r) "Hier beghint die lange vigilie".
Also described by MMDC and A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague).
